text: Richard W. Hinch (May 1, 1949 â€“ December 9, 2020) was an American Republican politician. He was a member and Speaker of the New Hampshire House of Representatives. He became speaker on December 2, 2020 just one week before his death. He was elected to the state house in 2008. Hinch was born in Marblehead, Massachusetts. Hinch died at his home in Concord, New Hampshire on December 9, 2020 from COVID-19, at age 71. ==References== Category:1949 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Deaths from the COVID-19 pandemic in the United States Category:Members of the New Hampshire General Court Category:Politicians from Massachusetts Category:Politicians from New Hampshire Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
